This paper deals with the problem of forgetting in generative models, specifically in generative adversarial networks (GANs). The paper proposes a new framework called Memory Replay GANs (MeRGANs) to address this problem. The paper also conducts experiments on image datasets such as MNIST, SVHN, and LSUN, which are commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of conditional GANs (cs.AI) and memory replay (cs.NE) to improve the performance of the model. Finally, the paper evaluates the quality of the generated images using both qualitative and quantitative metrics, which is a common practice in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV).
